name: Heather Bruggeman
caption: "Floor finishing was halted by Emily"s arrival and my desire to create some semblance of home for the week. Time ran out before I could get three coats on. I stressed about it for a day as I realized I wouldn"t make my deadline, but then I smartened up because what was the point in stressing. None of the floors were raw wood, they all had at least one coat of finish this one had two. I"d put new felt pads on the feet of the few furniture pieces we"d use, and our own sock feet would be safe enough. I"d finish the job after Thanksgiving. Not ideal, but not exactly a real problem. I might have run out of time to get the floors finished before Emily"s arrival, but the nice thing about being 46 is I sweat the small stuff less and less... and this sort of thing really is small stuff. âœ¨ Choosing floor finish was unexpectedly emotional for me. Painting, paperhanging, and wood finishing was my father"s trade for over fifty years. This is the first project I"ve done without his advice, and I so desperately wanted to talk to him. I don"t have enough room here to tell the story of how I finally chose the floor product I"m using, but it turns out he was talking to me the whole time. I just needed to pay attention. But even as I struggled to listen and choose a product, I was raised to know this: When the man at the paint store gives you two choices, asking if you want semi or high gloss floor finish, you say,  Neither. I"d like satin, please.  And your floors will be warm and soft and luminous. ðŸŒŸ"

name: The Rock Campus
caption: "#TRCrockhistory  30 tahun lalu pada hari ini, Guns & Roses merilis album ke 2 mereka \"Lies\". Sebelum ini GnR butuh waktu setahunan untuk album debut major label mereka \"Appetite For Destruction\" mencapai no. 1 di charts Billboard & mendominasi rock mainstream. Bahkan GnR udah mulai proses produksi album berikutnya ketika album tsb mulai meledak. Mereka pun menghentikan proses rekaman n meneruskan lg tour. Album Appetite melahirkan bbrp hit single besar sehingga jadual tour mereka menjadi semakin padat & semakin lama. Geffen Records label band ini memutuskan bahwa mereka hrs merilis album di tahun 1988 sebelum kelamaan mumpung GnR msh panas di charts. \"Lies\" jg adalah album terakhir mrk bersama drummer Steven Adler. Jadi album \"Lies\" yang dipasarkan sebagai full studio album ini sebetulnya adalah kompilasi lagu2 GnR yg sebagian nya di rekam terburu buru. Bukan sesuatu yg dikonsep sebagai full album. Axl Rose mengaku benci dgn vokal nya krn dlm keadaan capek dr jadual tour yg padat. Menggabungkan EP \"Live ?!*@ Live Like A Suicide\" & 4 track akustik yg nyeleneh & apa adanya album ini tetap dilahap oleh fans GnR n meledak juga di chart. Lagu \"Patience\" dgn siulan Axl adalah satu2nya single lagu ini. \"Lies" berhasil terjual 8 juta unit.  Strategi Geffen Records ini berhasil krn album berikut mereka ternyata butuh waktu 3 tahunan lg sebelum dirilis n band ini udah mengalami berbagai masalah internal yg berhujung dgn bubarnya GnR. . Apa lagu fav loe dari album ini? ðŸ”¥ . #THEROCKCAMPUS #guecadas #rockhistory #gunsnroses #lies #rock"

name: The Rock Campus
caption: "#TRCrockhistory Pada hari ini di tahun 1982 Ozzy Ozbourne merilis album live "Speak Of The Devil". Ini adalah satu2nya album yg di isi oleh gitaris Brad Gillis sebelum dia bergabung dgn band hard rock Night Ranger & juga penampilan rekaman pertama bassist Rudy Sarzo bersama Ozzy. Brad Gillis menggantikan Randy Rhoads yg meninggal dunia beberapa bulan sebelum "Speak Of The Devil" diproduksi. Album live ini cukup populer di US & UK tapi anehnya materi album ini berisi cover lagu2 Black Sabbath sedangkan para musisi personil di album ini yang tour bersama Ozzy juga membawakan lagu2 dr album solo Ozzy. Ironisnya sang ikon metal ini sendiri sempat gak mengakui album ini yg katanya hanya dirilis krn dia masih berhutang 2 album kepada label Jet Records. Masih blm jelas kenapa album live solo Ozzy bersama gitaris Randy Rhoads saat itu dibatalkan n versi ini yang justru dirilis. Barangkali Ozzy msh sedang berduka saat itu karena dia memang sangat terpukul atas berpulangnya Randy Rhoads. . #THEROCKCAMPUS #guecadas #rockhistory #ozzyozbourne"

name: LSPR DANCE
caption: "LET US INTRODUCE YOU TO ONE OF THE CHOREOGRAPHER OF DANCE ON 4: The Creation  Wandy Adrianus, dancer and also one of the choreographer at United Dance Works Jakarta who is very talented in dancing going to amused you with his choreography on Dance On 4  These are his journeys -Dancer & Teacher at Forever Dance Center, Jakarta (2008-2010) -Dancer & Cast of Aladdin in Ballet by Marlupi Dance Academy (2010) -Dancer & Choreographer at United Dance Works, Jakarta (2011-present) -Dancer of Dance On The Musical by Namarina Youth Dance -Coach & Talent Indonesia Mencari Bakat 3 Trans TV (2012) -Coach & Talent for X-Factor Indonesia RCTI (2013) -Choreographer "The Thing (2014)", "BPP" (2016), "ONCE" (2017), "Roots Of Love (2017)", "Art Effect" (2018) at Dance Generations & Urban Youth Dance Theater -Coach & Dancer of Indonesia Mencari Bakat Trans TV (2011-2014) -Choreographer of Indonesia Nickelodeon Kids Choice Awards Global TV (2012-2018) -Ambassador of Indonesia Bisa (Badan Ekonomi Kreatif) by kabarindo.com in Hongkong (2014) -Stage Act Instructor for Nyar & Angela Nazar (2015) -Cast of Sunshine Becomes You Movie, by Rocky Soraya -Talent for Kratingdaeng TVC (2015) -Dancer & Choreographer for Rossa Konser Pesona Cinta in Johor Bharu Malaysia (2015) -Dancer & Cast of Land Of Oz in Ballet by Namarina Dance Academy (2017) -Choreographer of #gueDECIDE Project by NewLand ID (2017) -Choreographer Vivo V9 Grand Launch Mini Musical at Candi Borobudur (2018) -Dancer for Hailee Steinfeld at Indonesian Choice Awards 5.0 NET"

But because I looked fine on the outside, most people assumed that I was ok. I wasnâ€™t.  How did I learn to manage? First, I had to learn how to make a CHOICE. To chose to fight back. When I felt symptoms coming on I could choose to focus on breathing. That may sound weird to you, but thatâ€™s literally where I could catch it. I would start with short guided meditation. And if I could use my breathing to relax, I was going to be ok. If I chose to focus on the anxiety and fear, I would choose the panic attack. But realizing that I had a choice was my first step forward.  Some things that I implemented at my own pace that really helped me: meditation, both guided and silent, gratitude, journaling, affirmations. I also confronted a lot of fear based beliefs in my life, first by identifying them, then diving deeper and seeing where those stories started. The beautiful thing is that we are all in charge of our own story. And if we donâ€™t like the one we are in, we can rewrite it.  I have found that there isnâ€™t any kind of â€œquick fixâ€. This stuff takes time, and is a PRACTICE. Connecting with yourself requires you to be alone, silent, and with your thoughts. So many of us fill our time because we fear that.  We fear really seeing who we are, deciding what we believe.
